x>arci\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan>\u003C/name> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>f\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>ilii\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003CorgName>\u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>Ouf\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>entina\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan>\u003C/orgName>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"4\"/>\u003Cname>Pollionis\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"5\"/>\u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>oper\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>is\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cname>\u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>C\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>ai\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan>\u003C/name> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cname>Domiti\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"6\"/>\u003Cname>\u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>C\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>ai\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan>\u003C/name> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>f\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>ilii\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>Vot\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>uria\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cname>Rufi\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"7\"/>\u003Corig>ALYPUS\u003C/orig> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Corig>SIMBUL\u003C/orig>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"8\"/>Mercurio\n                    \u003Clb n=\"9\"/>Augusto\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\n                    \u003Capp>\u003Cnote>Text: CIL\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                    \u003Capp loc=\"line 5\">\u003Cnote>Mommsen oper(a) vel oper(is) opinor\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#AA\">\n                \u003Cp>[By the order of?] Marcus Albus Pollio, son of Marcus, of [tribe] Oufentina, for the work of Gaius Domitius Rufus, son of Gaius, of [tribe] Voturia, ALYPUS SIMBUL. To Mercury Augustus.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\">\n                \u003Cp>Manganaro suggests 'ex testamento' rather than 'iussu', and notes that the onomastics are Domitianic. SIMBVL is suggested by Mommsen possibly to be a transliteration of συμβολαιογράφος, a suggestion broadly followed by Manganaro.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"CIL\">\n                        \u003Cauthor>Mommsen\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1883\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>\n                            \u003Cref target=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/books/CILv10pII1883\">7224\u003C/ref>\n                        \u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/GQN8UZSI\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Manganaro\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1988\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>50, 69, 72\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/RZSFKACR\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Kragelund\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>2008\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>120 n.15\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/8CZHBMK9\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001895\">https://biblio.i